text: Entry of the main structure thumb Casteddu di Tappa is a Bronze Age archaeological site of the Torreann Culture, in Corsica. It is located in the commune of Porto-Vecchio. ==See also== *Prehistory of Corsica ==References== * Le gisement torréen fortifié de Tappa, Porto-Vecchio (Corse), Roger Grosjean, at Persee Category:Archaeological sites in Corsica
title: Casteddu di Tappa
